rComments: Teaches much too broadly for students to actually learn something of substance...grades hard on essays. He is amusing, but I wouldn't take his class again unless required.

He was very very hepful with the essay and any questions I had about course work and other history stuff. His class was boring at times but overall it wasn't too bad. He can be quite funny at times and is really easy to talk to. TAKE HIS CLASS!
Pretty good prof. Funny and quick to reply to questions via email. I would take another class with him.

One of the most entertaining and helpful professors I ever had. Makes class interesting and hilarious. Who knew history could be so funny? Sometimes says things you will have to think about for a day or two in order to understand its full context with the world and yourself. Do take his class.

Wallace likes to scare students by not giving them much info about the essay assignment and final exam.  However, he's not that bad of a marker.  His classes are however boring and there is much gobbleybook on his slides (he doesn't post slides). Do memorize important dates for the final.  Do take his class
